Difference between <ul> and <ol>:

<ul> means Unordered List.
It shows bullet points and is used when order does not matter.
Example: Navigation menu, shopping list.

<ol> means Ordered List.
It shows numbering or letters and is used when order matters.
Example: Steps to build a website, ranking list.

Navigation menus use type="none" because the menu is still semantically a list.
Only the bullets are hidden using CSS instead of removing the <ul> tag.
